title: Static Analysis

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground

android.permission.SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW.description: Allows an application to show system-alert windows. Malicious applications can take over the entire screen of the phone.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADMIN.description: Allows applications to discover and pair bluetooth devices.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH.description: Allows applications to connect to paired bluetooth devices.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.GET_TASKS.description: Allows application to retrieve information about currently and recently running tasks. May allow malicious applications to discover private information about other applications.

android.permission.REORDER_TASKS.description: Allows an application to move tasks to the foreground and background. Malicious applications can force themselves to the front without your control.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.PACKAGE_USAGE_STATS.description: Allows the modification of collected component usage statistics. Not for use by common applications.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

manifest_analysis.title:
Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.
manifest_analysis.name: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App [android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]

playstore_details.title: App Blocker: Stay Focused & No Distractions
playstore_details.description:
BlockApps is a smart app that lets you block intrusive and distracting apps so that you can concentrate on the work at hand. BlockApps enables you to block individual apps or multiple apps at a time by creating blocking profiles. Select a group of apps that you'd like to block from the list of apps on your phone. This app can also be used by concerned parents who would like to limit and control their kids' phone usage using 'Strict Mode.'

What is the Strict Mode?

The strict mode serves as a parental lock that works on further enforcing the blocking of apps. It is a premium feature that can only be accessed by pro users. The strict mode works on top of profiles and individual apps the user has blocked.

Once the strict mode is switched on, the user cannot.
Uninstall the app blocker app.
Access the phone settings.
Access the app blocker app.
To unlock BlockApps, the user will have to enter a secure PIN set up before enabling strict mode. Only then can the user access the app and switch off strict mode.

What happens if you forget your PIN?

Don't worry! BlockApps will let the user set up a recovery method in which he/she will have to enter their email id and verify. In case the user forgets the pin, an OTP will be sent to this email id, and by entering the OTP, the user can access the app.

Blocking Modes
Quick Mode
This mode will block your apps indefinitely without setting any conditions. It will block your apps on the spot without an end date.

Usage Limit
This mode lets the user block an app or a group of apps by the time spent on them. Users can block by minutes spent in an hour or hours spent in a day. The user can schedule it by selecting days in a week

Time Intervals
By selecting this, the user can block apps from opening during a specific time of day. This feature can also be used to create a usage schedule where the user can only use their favorite apps during a particular period in a day.

Number of Launches
Users can block an app or a group of apps by the no of launches in a day or hour.

Block Notifications(PRO Only)
The block notification feature will block all incoming notifications when enabled and store them within the app. The user can tap on the bell icon at the top right of the top bar to access all blocked notifications.

Other Features
Blocking Profiles
With blocking profiles, the user can block multiple apps together by adding them to the profiles. Users can create specific profiles based on app categories such as social media, finance & games, etc. All the blocking mode will be as is. The user can activate or pause any profile at any time.

Website Blocker
Users can block distracting websites where they tend to spend a lot of time. You can block any website by a URL or a keyword in the URL.

App Usage Tracker
Users can find their phone and app usage information with metrics like time spent on device or app & the no of launches over a given period. The user can filter this data by time by using the time filter dropdown menu.
Tapping on any app will reveal more information such as last launch, total time used, data used & usage rank.

Pro Features
1) Strict Mode
2) Block Notifications
3) Remove ads

Why you need BlockApps?

In the smartphone age, where knowledge & sources of entertainment are just a few taps away, there are too many distractions around that stop us from getting our work done. More and more children are getting addicted to their phones and not engaging in age-appropriate activities like playing sport & studying. BlockApps aims to address this crisis by blocking access to apps that annoy and distract so that you or your kids can focus on important things that matter.
